text: @FedExHelp Just wanted to let you know that your customer service has been a nightmare. I've been shouted at, misled, redirected to unhelpful people, and now will be driving over an hour to retrieve a package at a place that may or may not be open.
@RedErinn Hi, this is Joseph  Thanks for reaching out.  Please DM your name, delivery address, tracking number, phone number, and email address.
@FedExHelp Why? I'm already going to have to go get it, maybe twice. It's been two days on the phone to get this far.
@RedErinn I apologize for any frustration this has caused you.  I hope that we have the opportunity to better serve you in the future.   ~Joseph.
